@REMARK ---------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Requirements" "PatchCX.guide/Requirements"
@PREV "Legal"
@NEXT "Installation"


@{JLEFT}
@{LINDENT 2}

@{B}patch.library@{UB}


You will find it on Aminet:util/libs/patchlib#?



@{B}PatchSetFunc@{UB}


You will find it on Aminet:util/misc/PatchSetFunc.#?


PatchSetFunc   patches   exec.libraries   SetFunction   function  to  use  the
patch.library.  PatchCX  is  quite useless without PatchSetFunc at the moment,
since neary all patches don't directly use the patch.library.



@{B}AmigaOS 3.0+@{UB}


The   gadtools.library  is  IMHO  unuseable  without  GT_GetGadgetAttrs.  This
function appeared first time in V39, so PatchCX needs AmigaOS 3.0+.



@{B}fd files@{UB}


You  don't  really  need  them,  but  PatchCX can't display any function names
without them.


If  you  don't  have  any  fd  file, you will find the fd files for the system
libraries on the Amiga Developer CD v1.1 in NDK_3.1/Includes&Libs/fd/#?


For  third  party  libraries  the  fd  files should be part of their developer
material, if there is any.



@{B}Patches ;-)@{UB}


I guess, most of you have already more than enough of them.

@ENDNODE
